Don't know what game he's planning?

250
00:22:36,867 --> 00:22:39,123
Great humiliation! Brutal cheating!

251
00:22:40,412 --> 00:22:43,583
Dharmaraja conducted the
Rajasuya Yagna to humiliate me.

252
00:22:44,151 --> 00:22:46,838
He built Mayasabha palace to undermine me.

253
00:22:47,375 --> 00:22:52,034
Vassal kings bowed
before him instead of me,

254
00:22:52,094 --> 00:22:54,115
and presented him with gifts and tax.

255
00:22:54,684 --> 00:22:58,919
And I myself distributed those gems
studded hampers to them and became a barl.

256
00:22:59,488 --> 00:23:03,850
Above all, I was laughed
at by imperious Draupadi.

257
00:23:04,522 --> 00:23:09,083
Before that humiliation burns me,
I'll sacrifice my life to fire.

258
00:23:09,642 --> 00:23:10,853
Arrange the pyre.

259
00:23:11,509 --> 00:23:14,732
O emperor! Why are you worried
when your friend Karna is here?

260
00:23:14,950 --> 00:23:16,030
Blow the trumpets of war.

261
00:23:16,337 --> 00:23:18,480
I'll kill Pandavas and repay my gratitude.

262
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:20,919
Well said Karna.
That's our immediate duty.

263
00:23:21,291 --> 00:23:25,583
Duryodhana, why use an axe for
something that can be clipped with a nail?

264
00:23:25,883 --> 00:23:27,859
Invite Dharmaraja for the game of dice.

265
00:23:28,248 --> 00:23:29,810
I'll simply play the game,

266
00:23:30,039 --> 00:23:35,547
effortlessly win their
kingdom and present it to you.

267
00:23:36,303 --> 00:23:38,816
Winning and losing in game
of dice is decided by God, Uncle.

268
00:23:39,234 --> 00:23:40,158
What if we lose?

269
00:23:40,292 --> 00:23:42,076
May this inauspicious
words never come true.

270
00:23:42,419 --> 00:23:46,388
My dice will never lose.
Test it. Come on.

271
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:48,868
Dushasana, tell me your number.

272
00:23:50,467 --> 00:23:51,086
Two!

273
00:23:54,050 --> 00:23:56,352
Wow uncle!
This is our immediate duty.

274
00:23:57,209 --> 00:23:58,611
Karna, you tell now.

275
00:23:59,647 --> 00:24:02,613
It's not heroic to hide our
strength and use contrivance.

276
00:24:03,218 --> 00:24:06,306
No problem, Warrior Karna. Test my skill.

277
00:24:06,953 --> 00:24:08,041
Two again.

278
00:24:09,773 --> 00:24:10,656
Wow uncle!

279
00:24:11,684 --> 00:24:13,817
Did you see Duryodhana?

280
00:24:14,306 --> 00:24:16,685
An idea in the brain and dice in hands,

281
00:24:17,025 --> 00:24:19,435
With them I can bring
a complete destruction.

282
00:24:20,096 --> 00:24:21,435
You test me too.

283
00:24:22,780 --> 00:24:26,966
-Third time is very important.
-Okay, I'll see. Same two.

284
00:24:27,794 --> 00:24:28,751
No, wait. One!

285
00:24:30,707 --> 00:24:31,654
Wow uncle!

286
00:24:32,132 --> 00:24:36,146
Did you see? The dice fell one
hesitantly when you asked hesitantly.

287
00:24:36,566 --> 00:24:38,868
-Invite Dharmaraja immediately.
-Yes brother.

288
00:24:39,076 --> 00:24:40,264
That's our immediate duty.

289
00:24:43,665 --> 00:24:46,305
Duryodhana, one more thing,

290
00:24:47,190 --> 00:24:51,502
Dharmaraja is impulsive gambler,
he goes berserk on losing,

291
00:24:51,884 --> 00:24:54,280
you make him stake not just
kingdom but his brothers,

292
00:24:54,623 --> 00:25:00,452
himself and their wife
Draupadi too and lose them.

293
00:25:01,038 --> 00:25:02,398
Now, it's your wish.

294
00:25:02,988 --> 00:25:05,628
I hope you'll achieve
what you said, uncle.

295
00:25:06,003 --> 00:25:09,177
Brother, uncle's idea is a cyclone.
A great cyclone!

296
00:25:09,378 --> 00:25:15,324
[earthquake]

297
00:25:25,785 --> 00:25:27,931
What's this bad omen, uncle?

298
00:25:28,094 --> 00:25:31,040
Bad omen at Shakuni's place? No way!

299
00:25:31,405 --> 00:25:33,656
This is a victory anthem for my plans.

300
00:25:33,983 --> 00:25:34,868
Don't get scared.

301
00:25:34,927 --> 00:25:36,648
Let all your fears vanish.

302
00:25:36,989 --> 00:25:38,465
Even Lord Krishna,

303
00:25:38,605 --> 00:25:41,855
who is biased in favour of the Pandavas
would understand the power of my dice.

304
00:25:42,006 --> 00:25:42,574
Let's go.

305
00:25:52,375 --> 00:25:58,398
[music]

306
00:26:01,318 --> 00:26:03,261
"Did you hear this, Yashoda?"

307
00:26:04,386 --> 00:26:06,300
"Did you hear this, Yashoda?"

308
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:12,475
"Did you hear about pranks of
your little mischief Krishna?"

309
00:26:16,983 --> 00:26:22,955
"I don't know anything,
I wasn't here at all"

310
00:26:26,162 --> 00:26:31,187
"What can we do about his behaviour?"

311
00:26:31,331 --> 00:26:33,187
Is he the one who eats butter or mud?

312
00:26:33,666 --> 00:26:38,143
"By supressing the sound of his anklets,
he enters house stealthily like a cat"

313
00:26:40,601 --> 00:26:45,213
"By supressing the sound of his anklets,
he enters house stealthily like a cat"

314
00:26:45,674 --> 00:26:49,790
"He brings down the pots
that are tied to the ceiling"

315
00:26:50,176 --> 00:26:54,450
"He brings down the pots
that are tied to the ceiling"

316
00:26:54,969 --> 00:26:56,613
"And drank all the milk"

317
00:26:57,461 --> 00:26:59,020
"Ate all the curd"

318
00:26:59,979 --> 00:27:01,480
"Swallowed all the butter"

319
00:27:02,434 --> 00:27:04,622
"How can I single handedly eat them?
Does it happen anywhere?"

320
00:27:04,944 --> 00:27:09,366
"Does it happen anywhere?"

321
00:27:09,788 --> 00:27:14,236
"Did you hear it, mother Yashoda?"

322
00:27:14,664 --> 00:27:18,999
"Did you hear the fabricated
stories of Gopikas?"

323
00:27:20,012 --> 00:27:23,330
What? See how he is blaming us.
Can he be caught even if we want to?

324
00:27:23,663 --> 00:27:28,767
"When all the ladies set a plan and
were waiting at every threshold"

325
00:27:31,533 --> 00:27:36,710
"When all the ladies set a plan and
were waiting at every threshold"

326
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:39,501
"Anklet clinking was heard in one's home"

327
00:27:42,052 --> 00:27:44,852
"Flute was being played in another's home"

328
00:27:50,114 --> 00:27:52,814
"Anklet clinking was heard in one's home"

329
00:27:52,822 --> 00:27:55,417
"Flute was being played in another's home"

330
00:27:55,707 --> 00:27:56,810
"Aha! Then, what?"

331
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:59,433
"When we went inside to
check who the thief was"

332
00:27:59,606 --> 00:28:02,311
"He jumped off from there magically"

333
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:08,982
"Ask your charming son how
he entered and escaped?"

334
00:28:09,112 --> 00:28:14,222
"Ask your charming son how
he entered and escaped?"

335
00:28:15,010 --> 00:28:16,718
"How would I know? I wasn't there"

336
00:28:16,911 --> 00:28:17,555
"Where were you then?"

337
00:28:17,903 --> 00:28:22,541
"Danced on the head of the snake, Kaliya
snake that poisoned the river Kalindi"

338
00:28:32,088 --> 00:28:36,587
"Danced on the head of the snake, Kaliya
snake that poisoned the river Kalindi"

339
00:28:36,877 --> 00:28:41,208
"I killed the snake and reared cattle"

340
00:28:41,596 --> 00:28:43,795
"I killed the snake and reared cattle"

341
00:28:44,100 --> 00:28:48,521
-"I killed the snake and reared cattle"-Hey Krishna!

342
00:28:49,047 --> 00:28:53,615
Hey Krishna... Mukunda...

343
00:28:54,310 --> 00:28:57,543
Won't you hear my appeal for help?

344
00:29:03,653 --> 00:29:09,671
"I don't have any other saviour than you"

345
00:29:10,755 --> 00:29:16,444
"Who will help this woman in distress...
Hey Krishna,"

346
00:29:17,651 --> 00:29:21,765
"Won't you see my pathetic condition?"

347
00:29:22,572 --> 00:29:24,548
-"Please listen..."
-Krishna! What is this?

348
00:29:27,375 --> 00:29:29,158
What's this?
What happened?

349
00:29:29,448 --> 00:29:32,728
What would it be?
There is no bound for Kauravas atrocities.

350
00:29:33,636 --> 00:29:36,746
Not only did they take away Pandavas
kingdom in their hexed game of dice,

351
00:29:37,316 --> 00:29:41,840
but also they've humiliated them
and and were sending them to exile.

352
00:29:41,987 --> 00:29:44,004
What! Such an injustice?

353
00:29:44,205 --> 00:29:46,473
-So evil minded!
-It is the egoistic pride of the Kauravas.

354
00:29:47,068 --> 00:29:48,762
We shouldn't tolerate this injustice!

355
00:29:49,497 --> 00:29:51,122
Brother, give an order.

356
00:29:51,246 --> 00:29:53,109
-I'll go with our army...
-Satyaki,

357
00:29:53,667 --> 00:29:54,577
Don't rush off.

358
00:29:55,196 --> 00:29:56,506
I too won't tolerate injustice.

359
00:29:57,304 --> 00:30:00,028
Now, I'll go to Hastinapura and
teach a lesson to Kauravas,

360
00:30:00,237 --> 00:30:01,925
and return the lost kingdom to Pandavas.

361
00:30:02,887 --> 00:30:05,934
Duryodhana is my disciple,
he'll never go against me.

362
00:30:06,467 --> 00:30:07,568
Get my chariot ready.

363
00:30:09,016 --> 00:30:09,682
Come dear.

364
00:30:10,598 --> 00:30:13,547
I've been fearing about
trickster, Shakuni's evil plans.

365
00:30:13,697 --> 00:30:15,537
No matter whatever someone does, it is
we who have to face the consequences.

366
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,908
Don't worry Sasi.
I'm there for them.

367
00:30:23,030 --> 00:30:24,198
Hail King!

368
00:30:24,475 --> 00:30:27,938
We've received a message about your
Guru Balarama visiting our kingdom.

369
00:30:28,961 --> 00:30:34,437
Sentry, take this for
bringing good news on time.

370
00:30:36,587 --> 00:30:39,224
How is it good news, Uncle? I'm scared.

371
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:42,998
We don't know the reason of his visit.
Moreover, he's short tempered.

372
00:30:43,034 --> 00:30:44,460
No problem, Duryodhana.

373
00:30:45,216 --> 00:30:47,794
Best remedy for short temper is praise.

374
00:30:48,052 --> 00:30:50,370
So arrange a grand
honour to Lord Balarama.

375
00:30:50,486 --> 00:30:52,235
He will be pleased with your felicitation,

376
00:30:52,310 --> 00:30:55,460
and grant you a boon without
even having a second thought.

377
00:30:55,752 --> 00:30:56,507
Take it.

378
00:30:59,838 --> 00:31:03,924
Get your son Lakshmana Kumar
married with his daughter Sasirekha.

379
00:31:04,247 --> 00:31:06,465
With that, Balarama will be on our side.

380
00:31:06,689 --> 00:31:08,515
Ultimately, Yadavas will be on our side.

381
00:31:08,740 --> 00:31:13,336
And with that, Krishna will be left
with no choice but to join our ranks.

382
00:31:13,422 --> 00:31:15,683
Wow Uncle!
That's our immediate duty.

383
00:31:15,762 --> 00:31:18,963
Uncle, politically our plan is flawless,

384
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:22,200
but our Lakshmana Kumar
is more proud than his father.

385
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:24,804
Will he accept the Yadava princess?

386
00:31:25,080 --> 00:31:28,468
Well, he will definitely accept.
That's my responsibility.

387
00:31:30,128 --> 00:31:36,078
[humming]

388
00:31:40,988 --> 00:31:42,057
-Sarathy
-My lord.

389
00:31:42,393 --> 00:31:43,019
[whistles]

390
00:31:44,284 --> 00:31:45,691
Wow! Amazing!

391
00:31:50,041 --> 00:31:51,038
-My lord!
-Yes.

392
00:31:53,304 --> 00:31:58,096
Great warrior, braveheart,
Lakshmana Kumar...

393
00:31:59,078 --> 00:32:00,605
-Enough of your praise.
-Okay.

394
00:32:00,789 --> 00:32:02,372
My lord, hear mine.

395
00:32:02,644 --> 00:32:07,767
You're life is honourable than Abhimanyu's

396
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:09,249
Wow! This is real poetry.

397
00:32:09,580 --> 00:32:10,086
Here, take it.

398
00:32:11,364 --> 00:32:12,497
Then, hear this.

399
00:32:12,932 --> 00:32:15,145
"Being exiled into a
forest is his ill-fate,"

400
00:32:15,285 --> 00:32:17,845
"Having lavish life is your good fate."

401
00:32:19,034 --> 00:32:19,811
Well said.

402
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:21,718
Hail prince!

403
00:32:22,889 --> 00:32:27,055
-My lord, you've got visitor.
-Not now.

404
00:32:27,877 --> 00:32:31,979
"In the battlefield, when a
Padmavyuha (Lotus strategy) is planned,"

405
00:32:32,414 --> 00:32:34,194
"Abhimanyu knows only to go forward,"

406
00:32:34,386 --> 00:32:36,087
"But you know how to turn back."

407
00:32:36,366 --> 00:32:37,132
[laughs]

408
00:32:37,336 --> 00:32:37,946
-My lord!
-Shh!

409
00:32:38,999 --> 00:32:40,308
"Has he got your brain?"

410
00:32:40,517 --> 00:32:42,012
"Has he got your ease?"

411
00:32:42,244 --> 00:32:43,637
"Has he got your mastery of art?"

412
00:32:43,896 --> 00:32:46,589
-"This is not a praise"
-Ha ha.

413
00:32:46,688 --> 00:32:47,818
Sarathy... Sarathy.

414
00:32:48,196 --> 00:32:51,924
My lord, they've praised
and accepted gifts.

415
00:32:52,062 --> 00:32:55,360
These blabbering poets are
nothing compared to me.

416
00:32:55,854 --> 00:32:57,108
-Hear mine.
-Yes.

417
00:32:57,439 --> 00:32:58,958
"Two that side, two this side,"

418
00:32:59,231 --> 00:33:00,983
"Abhimanyu's uncles"

419
00:33:01,518 --> 00:33:05,696
"From either side,
they are just four."

420
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,528
"But for you,"

421
00:33:07,833 --> 00:33:11,988
"You've got one less of hundred uncles."

422
00:33:12,211 --> 00:33:16,666
What an army of uncles you have!

423
00:33:16,874 --> 00:33:21,502
-"Wonderful..."
-Well said, Sarathy.

424
00:33:23,068 --> 00:33:24,467
Dear Lakshmana Kumara!

425
00:33:25,774 --> 00:33:28,552
Oh is it you?
You all may leave now.

426
00:33:32,259 --> 00:33:36,318
Wow! You look very handsome.
A romantic hero indeed.

427
00:33:37,761 --> 00:33:40,090
I'll tell you good news,
come sit here.

428
00:33:40,698 --> 00:33:42,867
It is the attribute of a brave
person to listen standing.

429
00:33:43,500 --> 00:33:43,954
Tell me.

430
00:33:44,552 --> 00:33:47,981
Look, you're the prince
of this vast kingdom.

431
00:33:48,673 --> 00:33:49,284
That's all?

432
00:33:50,334 --> 00:33:52,825
Not just that,
you're the prince of princes.

433
00:33:53,149 --> 00:33:54,470
Young king!

434
00:33:54,671 --> 00:33:56,050
Young emperor!

435
00:33:57,292 --> 00:34:02,027
Your father and I've decided
that we should get you married.

436
00:34:02,090 --> 00:34:03,353
Then, I've decided too.

437
00:34:04,635 --> 00:34:06,662
The proposal is also
from a very good family.

438
00:34:07,190 --> 00:34:08,993
The bride is a world beauty.

439
00:34:09,066 --> 00:34:12,144
Sasirekha, Balarama's daughter.

440
00:34:12,250 --> 00:34:12,870
What a shame!

441
00:34:13,549 --> 00:34:16,626
How can I become the son-in-law to
uncivilised liege king of Yadavas?

442
00:34:16,933 --> 00:34:17,539
Impossible.

443
00:34:18,762 --> 00:34:20,260
That's a danger.

444
00:34:20,832 --> 00:34:22,861
We've heard that Abhimanyu loves her.

445
00:34:23,089 --> 00:34:25,407
What!
Is it me who can't love her?

446
00:34:25,730 --> 00:34:27,931
I'll marry any girl Abhimanyu loves.

447
00:34:28,251 --> 00:34:30,056
I'll ensure that there are no girls
left in this world for him to marry.

448
00:34:30,404 --> 00:34:31,740
Grandpa, I want Rekha.

449
00:34:32,571 --> 00:34:35,163
-You're smart!
-Yes.

450
00:34:35,565 --> 00:34:37,762
-Then I'll fix the marriage.
-Your wish.

451
00:34:51,027 --> 00:34:53,490
Hail victory to you!

452
00:34:53,498 --> 00:34:55,009
Epitome of truth!

453
00:34:55,033 --> 00:34:56,263
Protector of the refuge seekers!

454
00:34:56,439 --> 00:34:57,831
Generous man!

455
00:34:57,932 --> 00:34:59,373
Saviour of the world!

456
00:34:59,598 --> 00:35:03,325
Supreme lord of the world,
Sri Sri Balarama!

457
00:35:03,425 --> 00:35:05,698
Hail victory to you!

458
00:35:05,899 --> 00:35:11,907
[music]

459
00:36:53,495 --> 00:36:56,056
Has he got your brain?

460
00:36:57,197 --> 00:36:59,415
Has he got your ease?

461
00:36:59,901 --> 00:37:02,276
Has he got your mastery of art?

462
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:05,146
-Who is it, Sarathy?
-You!

463
00:37:06,229 --> 00:37:07,707
No... I mean Abhimanyu.

464
00:37:08,916 --> 00:37:11,910
"Victory to you, O mighty warrior!"

465
00:37:11,971 --> 00:37:14,525
"Victory to you, O romantic hero!"

466
00:37:14,796 --> 00:37:17,246
"Lullaby." Stop your lullaby!

467
00:37:17,339 --> 00:37:18,002
Okay.

468
00:37:18,457 --> 00:37:22,965
My lord, come quickly and
seek blessings from Balarama.

469
00:37:23,163 --> 00:37:25,258
Shame! Taking is seeker's trait.

470
00:37:25,548 --> 00:37:27,507
-Giving is regal character.
-So be it!

471
00:37:27,904 --> 00:37:32,060
My lord, if you delay like this,
you may not get Sasirekha.

472
00:37:32,300 --> 00:37:35,546
You promised to bow to
your future father-in-law.

473
00:37:35,639 --> 00:37:38,280
Not bow, I promised only to greet him.

474
00:37:38,833 --> 00:37:41,392
-How to do it?
-It's simple, my lord.

475
00:37:41,748 --> 00:37:44,681
-Fold hands like this...
-Shame! That's your habit.

476
00:37:44,715 --> 00:37:45,232
So be it.

477
00:37:45,759 --> 00:37:47,568
My lord, I'll show you.

478
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:50,091
You've seen Dharmaraja

479
00:37:50,299 --> 00:37:53,691
greeting Bhishma, Dronacharya
and your grandfather, didn't you?

480
00:37:54,067 --> 00:37:55,239
And you used to laugh jeeringly at him.

481
00:37:55,758 --> 00:37:58,255
Even though it is little
difficult, bend like this

482
00:37:58,590 --> 00:38:00,377
with profound humbleness,

483
00:38:00,604 --> 00:38:05,870
-Bend like this... and that's all, my lord
-I can go down further, get up.

484
00:38:06,707 --> 00:38:07,124
Come.

485
00:38:09,513 --> 00:38:14,777
Moreover, the game of dice was played with
Bheeshma, Drona, Vidhura's permission

486
00:38:14,849 --> 00:38:16,404
and in their presence.

487
00:38:17,942 --> 00:38:20,654
If there was injustice
would they keep quiet?

488
00:38:20,961 --> 00:38:25,653
Yes, winning fairly in the game of
dice is equal as just as winning a war.

489
00:38:26,135 --> 00:38:26,955
I too accept it.

490
00:38:27,301 --> 00:38:30,556
Not only you, even Dharmaraja
himself accepted it.

491
00:38:30,794 --> 00:38:35,137
But Bhima got furious and
made vows of destruction.

492
00:38:35,933 --> 00:38:40,320
Uncle, don't talk about that
blabber and hurt his feelings.

