00:59:21,076 --> 00:59:22,908
Hail the mighty majestic,
his royal highness!

744
00:59:23,211 --> 00:59:25,779
Stop!
I'll get you gifts.

745
00:59:26,131 --> 00:59:28,510
Praising me coming to my place.

746
00:59:28,629 --> 00:59:31,570
Then what? You're the supreme lord!

747
00:59:31,678 --> 00:59:34,931
Yes... but I didn't expect you so early.

748
00:59:35,089 --> 00:59:36,179
Why should you think, brother?

749
00:59:36,501 --> 00:59:39,265
You're kind hearted boon giver,
don't know what boon you granted them.

750
00:59:39,731 --> 00:59:42,359
May be he's here to remind
you, lest you may forget it.

751
00:59:42,523 --> 00:59:44,339
Why should I remind him, Krishna?

752
00:59:44,553 --> 00:59:46,879
The moment he granted
the boon we were blessed.

753
00:59:47,008 --> 00:59:49,334
Yes... Great men don't come for nothing.

754
00:59:49,712 --> 00:59:50,210
Brother...

755
00:59:50,562 --> 00:59:53,946
Whatever it is, I'll not tolerate
if he plays game of dice with you.

756
00:59:54,607 --> 00:59:55,990
Why are you so scared, Krishna?

757
00:59:56,458 --> 00:59:58,465
It is obvious that your
brother will win the game of dice.

758
00:59:59,793 --> 01:00:00,977
He's epitome of honesty.

759
01:00:01,218 --> 01:00:04,625
But if it is proved you're dishonest,
you'll have trouble from him.

760
01:00:06,208 --> 01:00:07,559
It's good for you to be careful.

761
01:00:08,118 --> 01:00:09,520
Though I'm younger it
just my sweet warning.

762
01:00:10,476 --> 01:00:14,477
Did you see how Krishna is
threatening with his wit?

763
01:00:14,688 --> 01:00:19,692
No, whenever he meets intelligent
men like you, he gets little shaken up.

764
01:00:20,542 --> 01:00:21,197
Welcome.

765
01:00:21,855 --> 01:00:22,414
Welcome.

766
01:00:24,931 --> 01:00:29,025
This auspicious time is fixed according
Lakshmana Kumar's horoscope.

767
01:00:29,763 --> 01:00:32,486
The event of wedding of Sasirekha

768
01:00:33,012 --> 01:00:34,945
will be an event that world will
remember for a very long time.

769
01:00:35,208 --> 01:00:38,507
The power of the
auspicious time is very strong.

770
01:00:39,283 --> 01:00:41,387
You've decided the auspicious time too.

771
01:00:42,030 --> 01:00:44,836
Of course. As soon as you said okay,

772
01:00:45,383 --> 01:00:49,224
Bheeshma, Drona and Vidhura
wanted this to happen at the earliest

773
01:00:49,565 --> 01:00:51,507
So they've sent us by fixing
this date and time of marriage.

774
01:00:53,052 --> 01:00:57,091
If elders had fixed this, I'm
sure it'll be very important.

775
01:00:59,101 --> 01:01:01,301
Why are you thinking, brother? Go ahead.

776
01:01:01,594 --> 01:01:02,093
So be it.

777
01:01:05,180 --> 01:01:08,058
I think our priests are checking
for the best auspicious dates.

778
01:01:08,456 --> 01:01:11,052
Wow! Great astrologers!

779
01:01:11,948 --> 01:01:15,793
They are very renowned astrologers.

780
01:01:17,962 --> 01:01:21,458
There's nothing to think
about this auspicious time.

781
01:01:21,670 --> 01:01:23,367
And even there is nothing
doubtful about this auspicious time.

782
01:01:23,623 --> 01:01:24,723
But still,

783
01:01:25,148 --> 01:01:28,098
We're checking planetary movements
according to the bride's horoscope.

784
01:01:28,850 --> 01:01:34,776
Shukracharya,
the guru of demons is casting a bad eye.

785
01:01:35,361 --> 01:01:39,513
This may create problems and difficulties
in the lives of the newly weds.

786
01:01:39,752 --> 01:01:45,740
Yes, astrology always says
right and bitter truths only.

787
01:01:46,370 --> 01:01:49,182
We must take only
the gist of it lightly.

788
01:01:50,096 --> 01:01:55,644
You've to take problem
here as love problem.

789
01:01:55,974 --> 01:02:01,025
Difficulties here mean many children.

790
01:02:01,829 --> 01:02:04,341
But this is bad time.

791
01:02:04,775 --> 01:02:08,174
Astrology says marriage
in these times is impossible.

792
01:02:08,428 --> 01:02:12,252
You need to be presented
for your scholarliness.

793
01:02:12,863 --> 01:02:15,282
But your astrology works
for ordinary people only,

794
01:02:15,643 --> 01:02:18,946
not for Kauravas who are
brilliant and fortunate men.

795
01:02:19,257 --> 01:02:23,678
May be but when Saturn is in this room...

796
01:02:23,879 --> 01:02:24,649
[chuckles]

797
01:02:24,832 --> 01:02:28,804
Our Shakuni who is equal
to a lakh Saturns is here,

798
01:02:28,892 --> 01:02:30,428
so why bother in which room the Saturn is?

799
01:02:30,814 --> 01:02:33,580
Accept it. It's their tradition.

800
01:02:35,235 --> 01:02:39,100
Brother, their haste is ours too.

801
01:02:39,724 --> 01:02:42,416
I too agree for this proposal
and the time fixed by them.

802
01:02:43,085 --> 01:02:44,877
Only if you think we don't
have much time.

803
01:02:45,842 --> 01:02:50,379
Krishna, when you're taking all
the responsibility in your hands,

804
01:02:51,577 --> 01:02:54,779
The time will never run short.
I don't have that fear.

805
01:02:55,558 --> 01:02:58,021
Alright. We shall fix
the wedding at this time.

806
01:03:13,580 --> 01:03:16,681
Amazing!
Sasirekha madam is very fortunate.

807
01:03:17,369 --> 01:03:19,236
She's going to wed Prince,
Lakshmana Kumara

808
01:03:19,467 --> 01:03:21,946
and become the daughter-in-law
of Queen Bhanumati...

809
01:03:22,224 --> 01:03:23,615
-Champa
-Madam.

810
01:03:29,354 --> 01:03:32,303
Be careful.
Mind your words. Get lost.

811
01:03:43,267 --> 01:03:44,385
[metal vessel tumbles]

812
01:03:45,088 --> 01:03:46,475
What's this barlishness, Sasi?

813
01:03:47,225 --> 01:03:50,746
How humiliated I would be if
people come to know your attitude?

814
01:03:54,028 --> 01:03:57,324
I plead you. Get groomed and come now.

815
01:03:57,981 --> 01:03:59,700
Grandpa Shakuni will bless you.

816
01:03:59,918 --> 01:04:03,208
I don't want any blessings.
I'm not interested in this wedding at all.

817
01:04:03,285 --> 01:04:06,261
Don't you say that. It is the
proposal which matches our status.

818
01:04:06,707 --> 01:04:08,301
And it is the wealth which came for us.

819
01:04:08,868 --> 01:04:11,251
Your dad gave his word to the
emperor for the welfare of you.

820
01:04:12,019 --> 01:04:13,010
Even your Uncle,
Krishna accepted this proposal.

821
01:04:13,711 --> 01:04:15,301
It is a lie. Everything is a lie.

822
01:04:15,480 --> 01:04:17,971
Your uncle himself sat with
them and approved the proposal.

823
01:04:18,597 --> 01:04:20,173
Let me ask him to say that to you.

824
01:04:20,426 --> 01:04:22,813
-I don't want anyone to tell me anything.
-My Queen

825
01:04:23,392 --> 01:04:25,529
Subhadra and Rukhmini have arrived.

826
01:04:25,766 --> 01:04:27,357
Everyone was holding grudge on me.

827
01:04:27,811 --> 01:04:28,710
What sin did I commit?

828
01:04:31,129 --> 01:04:35,482
Is it justice to break a promise of making
Sasi my daughter-in-law, brother?

829
01:04:35,672 --> 01:04:39,080
Is it breaking a promise?
He told it just like that to his sister.

830
01:04:39,589 --> 01:04:42,718
Will it be same as granting a boon
to emperor Duryodhana in his court?

831
01:04:43,335 --> 01:04:47,394
Not only that, you're making a
wedding alliance with of our enemies.

832
01:04:47,716 --> 01:04:49,411
Did you think it's a great insult to me?

833
01:04:50,390 --> 01:04:53,850
How my husband his
brothers look down upon me?

834
01:04:54,480 --> 01:04:56,344
If you think there would be such
treatment, then don't go there at all.

835
01:04:57,293 --> 01:04:59,013
There's nothing short
in your respect here.

836
01:04:59,150 --> 01:05:02,526
Enough of your respect for me, brother.
I'm telling you the last time,

837
01:05:03,219 --> 01:05:05,801
If Sasi doesn't become my daughter-in-law,
I'll not stay here even for a moment.

838
01:05:06,089 --> 01:05:07,393
Is this how you're going to threaten us?

839
01:05:07,918 --> 01:05:11,225
Do you want my daughter also
to be in parents' home like you?

840
01:05:12,987 --> 01:05:17,713
Sister, leave about Subhadra.
Think about our daughter.

841
01:05:18,487 --> 01:05:20,403
It is we who filled her
thoughts since childhood.

842
01:05:21,010 --> 01:05:24,245
Sasi hopes that Abhimanyu
will become her husband.

843
01:05:24,842 --> 01:05:27,575
If you marry her to someone else,
what will become of her life?

844
01:05:27,678 --> 01:05:29,578
Do you know about a daughter more than me?

845
01:05:30,110 --> 01:05:31,496
You would know had you
given birth to a daughter.

846
01:05:31,624 --> 01:05:32,411
Would you say these morals then?

847
01:05:32,960 --> 01:05:34,395
Revathi, keep quiet.

848
01:05:35,108 --> 01:05:38,632
Whatever it is, this wedding
would be conducted as scheduled.

849
01:05:39,521 --> 01:05:41,306
I don't want anyone
to stop or threaten me.

850
01:05:41,941 --> 01:05:42,941
Surely you do, brother.

851
01:05:43,706 --> 01:05:45,716
You're ruining two young
people's lives cosnciously.

852
01:05:46,365 --> 01:05:47,926
I didn't think you'll be so obstinate.

853
01:05:48,686 --> 01:05:50,835
Making your sibling sad
wouldn't just go waste.

854
01:05:51,499 --> 01:05:55,231
May be you think wealth of Kauravas
is greater than courage of Pandavas.

855
01:05:55,508 --> 01:05:56,232
It will never be true.

856
01:05:56,547 --> 01:05:59,026
Are you threatening me with
their bravery, Subhadra?

857
01:06:00,260 --> 01:06:04,362
Their bravery doesn't need me,
my disciple Duryodhana is enough.

858
01:06:05,035 --> 01:06:09,121
Even 1000 Bhimas and 1000 Arjunas
are nothing compared to him.

859
01:06:09,264 --> 01:06:14,241
Uncle, mind your tongue.
Though my father is not present, I'm here.

860
01:06:15,261 --> 01:06:17,104
-What will you do?
-What will I do?

861
01:06:17,322 --> 01:06:21,215
Abhimanyu, will you bring an insult
to me by going against your uncle?

862
01:06:21,597 --> 01:06:24,992
This is not a mutiny.
I'm standing bravely on my ground.

863
01:06:26,321 --> 01:06:29,567
Uncle, if Kauravas are
as brave as you say,

864
01:06:30,066 --> 01:06:31,978
tell them to come along
with Lakshmana Kumara,

865
01:06:32,650 --> 01:06:34,679
I'll drive out Duryodhana,
Dushyasana, Karna and Shakuni,

866
01:06:35,188 --> 01:06:38,343
and their armies to Hastinapuram,

867
01:06:38,647 --> 01:06:41,011
I'll take Sasi as my wife
in open competition.

868
01:06:41,519 --> 01:06:44,167
If you and your friends have the courage,
announce a Swayamvara.

869
01:06:44,479 --> 01:06:46,038
You'll know who Sasi belongs to.

870
01:06:46,804 --> 01:06:49,208
Abhimanyu,
why are you throwing challenges?

871
01:06:50,121 --> 01:06:51,937
If you are really a brave man,

872
01:06:52,291 --> 01:06:55,253
would you stand here and throw challenges?

873
01:07:02,684 --> 01:07:06,347
Subhadra, you're a brave
wife and a brave mother.

874
01:07:06,784 --> 01:07:08,255
I didn't expect you to be so weak.

875
01:07:09,625 --> 01:07:12,707
You understood Balarama's intentions,
right? Why do you still make a scene?

876
01:07:13,562 --> 01:07:15,298
There is no one here to
to listen to your appeals.

877
01:07:16,392 --> 01:07:17,810
You can go wherever you feel like.

878
01:07:18,695 --> 01:07:19,935
Sure, brother.

879
01:07:21,783 --> 01:07:26,216
The day when you honour
bravery but not wealth,

880
01:07:26,682 --> 01:07:28,354
I'll step here again only on that day.

881
01:07:30,288 --> 01:07:30,995
Aunt!

882
01:07:31,949 --> 01:07:34,096
-Aunt!
-Where are you going, Sasi?

883
01:07:34,864 --> 01:07:37,258
-I'll also go with aunt.
-When I'm still alive?

884
01:07:37,537 --> 01:07:39,534
Don't get smart with me.
Come.

885
01:07:39,855 --> 01:07:41,811
-Aunt.
-Sasi, what's this?

886
01:07:52,439 --> 01:07:53,015
Dharuka,

887
01:07:56,680 --> 01:07:59,139
Subhadra and Abhimanyu
are leaving to Dwaithavanam.

888
01:07:59,464 --> 01:08:03,048
But you've to take them to Ghatotkacha's
ashram without informing them.

889
01:08:03,188 --> 01:08:03,690
That's all.

890
01:08:11,748 --> 01:08:17,764
[music]

891
01:08:39,001 --> 01:08:44,049
"O God"

892
01:08:44,151 --> 01:08:47,093
"Your illusion is amazing"

893
01:08:48,161 --> 01:08:53,175
"O God"

894
01:08:53,369 --> 01:08:56,421
"Your illusion is amazing"

895
01:08:56,958 --> 01:09:00,557
"Your illusion is really amazing"

896
01:09:14,202 --> 01:09:17,531
"It's a himiliation to one
and happiness to another"

897
01:09:17,741 --> 01:09:21,195
"And it is entertainment to
you who knows everything"

898
01:09:25,035 --> 01:09:30,328
"Who is your person and who is above you?"

899
01:09:34,278 --> 01:09:37,846
"Who is your person and who is above you?"

900
01:09:38,203 --> 01:09:41,749
"Even the fate doesn't know it lord!"

901
01:09:41,958 --> 01:09:45,077
"Your illusion is amazing"

902
01:09:45,572 --> 01:09:51,567
[music]

903
01:09:58,625 --> 01:10:02,269
"The world in a tug of war
between happiness and sorrow"

904
01:10:02,431 --> 01:10:05,501
"is your playground"

905
01:10:09,588 --> 01:10:13,308
"Your tales of playing and illusions"

906
01:10:18,790 --> 01:10:22,202
"Your tales of playing and illusions"

907
01:10:22,546 --> 01:10:26,081
"The people who know
about them are fortunate"

908
01:10:26,430 --> 01:10:29,455
"Your illusion is amazing"

909
01:10:30,114 --> 01:10:35,000
"O God"

910
01:10:35,245 --> 01:10:38,251
"Your illusion is amazing"

911
01:10:38,846 --> 01:10:42,486
"Your illusion is really amazing"

912
01:10:43,062 --> 01:10:49,049
[music]

913
01:11:04,509 --> 01:11:10,498
[trumpets]

914
01:11:11,012 --> 01:11:16,977
[trumpets]

915
01:11:28,899 --> 01:11:30,020
Hmmm...

916
01:11:30,915 --> 01:11:31,969
-Dundubhi!
-Present sir!

917
01:11:32,174 --> 01:11:33,065
-Dundhura!
-Present sir!

918
01:11:33,303 --> 01:11:34,916
-Ugra! Bagra!-Present sir!

919
01:11:35,115 --> 01:11:35,420
Present sir!

920
01:11:35,690 --> 01:11:36,913
-Gaggolaka!
-Present sir!

921
01:11:37,369 --> 01:11:38,884
-Gandaragolaka!
-Present sir!

922
01:11:39,448 --> 01:11:40,992
-Utchhasura!
-Present sir!

923
01:11:41,432 --> 01:11:42,863
-Jatasura!
-Present sir!

924
01:11:43,271 --> 01:11:44,606
Rambu! Jambu!

925
01:11:45,953 --> 01:11:46,820
Rambu! Jambu!

926
01:11:48,125 --> 01:11:49,591
-Rambu! Jambu!
-Present sir!

927
01:11:49,709 --> 01:11:52,432
Present sir!
[yawns]

928
01:11:54,989 --> 01:11:58,649
If you study well as I instruct,
I'll clear your language difficulties.

929
01:11:58,849 --> 01:12:02,413
If not, Ghatotkacha will
come and thrash you.

930
01:12:02,614 --> 01:12:06,004
Master, our life is
linked with your lessons.

931
01:12:06,018 --> 01:12:07,216
Come on, teach us.

932
01:12:10,323 --> 01:12:10,956
Repeat!

933
01:12:11,635 --> 01:12:13,199
Su... ou... chus

934
01:12:13,552 --> 01:12:15,242
Group repeats:
Su... ou... chus

935
01:12:16,234 --> 01:12:17,848
Am... ou... chus.

936
01:12:18,409 --> 01:12:19,736
Group repeats:
Am... ou... chus.

937
01:12:20,611 --> 01:12:22,227
Dra... bhyou... bhis.

938
01:12:22,792 --> 01:12:24,319
Group repeats:
Dra... bhyou... bhis.

939
01:12:24,809 --> 01:12:25,508
[groans]

940
01:12:25,875 --> 01:12:27,468
Je... bhyom... bhyas.

941
01:12:28,287 --> 01:12:29,988
Group repeats:
Je... bhaya... bhass.

942
01:12:30,756 --> 01:12:32,033
Oh Shiva!

943
01:12:32,286 --> 01:12:33,458
Group repeats:
Oh Shiva!

944
01:12:33,799 --> 01:12:34,319
Shh!

945
01:12:34,520 --> 01:12:35,113
Group repeats:
Shh!

946
01:12:35,661 --> 01:12:37,462
-Hey Rambu! Bhyam.
-Bhayam.

947
01:12:38,701 --> 01:12:39,500
-Jambu.
-What?

948
01:12:39,701 --> 01:12:40,351
-Bhyas
-Bhass.

949
01:12:40,805 --> 01:12:42,141
Oh Shiva!

950
01:12:42,342 --> 01:12:43,236
Group repeates:
Oh Shiva!

951
01:12:43,652 --> 01:12:44,749
[groans]
[groans back]

952
01:12:44,950 --> 01:12:46,909
You are called leaders.
Can't you even repeat?

953
01:12:47,132 --> 01:12:47,821
Can't you pronounce?

954
01:12:48,022 --> 01:12:50,027
What if we can't pronounce? We will dance!

955
01:12:50,590 --> 01:12:53,492
"Here we go around, now we jump!"

956
01:12:53,779 --> 01:12:56,001
-Now we jump! Now we jump!
-Hey Rambu Jambu!

957
01:12:56,451 --> 01:13:01,050
[indistinctive loud singing]
-Hey Jambu!

958
01:13:01,990 --> 01:13:04,084
[drums playing]

959
01:13:05,820 --> 01:13:10,650
Ghatotkacha

960
01:13:11,104 --> 01:13:16,179
-Ghatotkacha
-Hail leader!

961
01:13:16,741 --> 01:13:20,534
"My flag must flutter"

962
01:13:20,741 --> 01:13:24,921
"on all eight directions"

963
01:13:25,391 --> 01:13:28,702
"Every demon, devil,"

964
01:13:28,987 --> 01:13:33,282
"elf on earth must worship me"

965
01:13:33,650 --> 01:13:38,627
"Wherever the place be"

966
01:13:38,800 --> 01:13:42,072
"wonders must happen upon my orders"

967
01:13:42,586 --> 01:13:47,887
"Even Gods and angels must say,"

968
01:13:48,124 --> 01:13:52,115
"Hail Ghatotkacha!"

969
01:13:52,349 --> 01:13:55,965
"I must rule this world"

970
01:13:56,266 --> 01:14:00,029
"I must acquire all the wealth"

971
01:14:00,455 --> 01:14:04,671
"I must make all our
relatives achieve greatness"

972
01:14:04,829 --> 01:14:09,686
"...and get all the glory!"

973
01:14:13,936 --> 01:14:18,252
Hail Leader!

974
01:14:19,937 --> 01:14:22,541
Chinamaya, my associates don't
need this education any more.

975
01:14:22,814 --> 01:14:24,483
They must learn the history and get
knowledge of friends and enemies.

976
01:14:24,763 --> 01:14:27,233
They should protect
friends and eat enemies.

977
01:14:27,452 --> 01:14:29,586
Hail Leader!

978
01:14:29,778 --> 01:14:32,149
-We'll eat!
-We'll eat enemies.

979
01:14:32,789 --> 01:14:33,677
Son!

980
01:14:36,563 --> 01:14:38,584
-Son! Son!
-Mother!

981
01:14:38,632 --> 01:14:41,372
I told you not to do this.
Whom are you attacking now?

982
01:14:41,546 --> 01:14:44,588
There is no war presently.
But I'm preparing for it, mother.

983
01:14:45,090 --> 01:14:48,217
King Bhimasena is your husband, my father,

984
01:14:48,782 --> 01:14:54,316
This is my preparation to wipe out those
evil Kauravas who betrayed them, mother.

985
01:14:54,332 --> 01:14:57,908
-That's a good deed, my son.
-Hail mother!

986
01:14:57,956 --> 01:14:59,166
-Hey Rambu
-Yes sir!

987
01:14:59,341 --> 01:15:00,824
-Hey Jambu
-Yes sir!

988
01:15:01,060 --> 01:15:05,068
-Our army must grow with every passing day
-Hail Leader!

989
01:15:05,983 --> 01:15:09,025
My dear associates,
develop an army of your own.

990
01:15:09,100 --> 01:15:10,854
Imprison anyone who crosses our path.

991
01:15:11,048 --> 01:15:15,757
-Hail Leader! [chariot moving sound]
-Aargh!

992
01:15:21,182 --> 01:15:24,603
Who is this charioteer
who dared to enter my area?

993
01:15:25,399 --> 01:15:28,374
-Kutasura
-Hail leader!

994
01:15:28,695 --> 01:15:29,287
Who is he?

995
01:15:29,593 --> 01:15:31,999
Make him say his name
and ask him to seek refuge.

996
01:15:32,028 --> 01:15:32,645
Hail Leader!

997
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:35,487
I consider only those who seek
my refuge as my associate. Go!

998
01:15:38,708 --> 01:15:39,704
[demonic spell]

999
01:15:50,099 --> 01:15:56,046
Go back and seek refuge.

1000
01:15:57,404 --> 01:16:00,458
Dharuka, what are these screams?
We can't see anyone.

1001
01:16:01,806 --> 01:16:07,543
[screams]

1002
01:16:08,359 --> 01:16:09,201
Why can't see anyone?

1003
01:16:12,003 --> 01:16:16,444
[screams]

1004
01:16:16,744 --> 01:16:18,272
Looks like magic world of demons!

1005
01:16:18,533 --> 01:16:20,458
Dharuka, we haven't taken
the wrong route, right?

1006
01:16:20,597 --> 01:16:22,610
This is right way.
We've entered it knowingly.

1007
01:16:22,624 --> 01:16:23,853
Or shall we go back?

1008
01:16:24,476 --> 01:16:27,171
Turning back is not our way. Go ahead.

1009
01:16:27,645 --> 01:16:32,473
Go back or seek refuge.

1010
01:16:33,230 --> 01:16:34,692
Why are you screaming invisibly?

1011
01:16:35,212 --> 01:16:38,245
If you've guts, appear before me,
I'll destroy your magic.

1012
01:16:38,624 --> 01:16:39,803
[screams]

1013
01:16:45,523 --> 01:16:49,778
-What's this? His magic is scary!
-Don't fear, keep going.

1014
01:16:54,240 --> 01:16:57,652
Hey lllusionist!
My arrow will kill you!

1015
01:16:59,054 --> 01:17:00,389
[groaning]

1016
01:17:01,755 --> 01:17:04,536
I surrender!

1017
01:17:05,818 --> 01:17:07,465
Victory is yours!

1018
01:17:20,338 --> 01:17:21,375
Carry on.

1019
01:17:23,192 --> 01:17:24,941
-Jambu
-Yes sir.

1020
01:17:26,066 --> 01:17:30,437
The Pandavas are friends.
It means our people.

1021
01:17:30,631 --> 01:17:31,242
Repeat now.

1022
01:17:31,601 --> 01:17:34,259
The Pandavas are frendz

1023
01:17:34,400 --> 01:17:37,117
Not frendz, say friends!

1024
01:17:37,243 --> 01:17:39,670
Say frendz! Not frendz.

1025
01:17:40,017 --> 01:17:42,983
King, he's teaching me now!
Ask him to say friends.

1026
01:17:43,165 --> 01:17:46,058
Why? We'll know our people
with that word, king.

1027
01:17:46,351 --> 01:17:47,127
Enough!

1028
01:17:47,457 --> 01:17:49,794
Knowledge is more
important than scholarliness.

1029
01:17:50,301 --> 01:17:51,325
Present him rope award!

1030
01:17:52,409 --> 01:17:53,032
Come on, put!

1031
01:17:56,064 --> 01:17:57,032
-Hey Rambu
-Yes, sir.

1032
01:17:57,233 --> 01:18:00,881
The Pandavas are friends.
What do you call their enemies Kauravas?

1033
01:18:01,443 --> 01:18:04,988
Anti frendz... Anti frendz.

1034
01:18:05,189 --> 01:18:06,837
You and your brain!

1035
01:18:07,039 --> 01:18:10,204
My lord, he has produced a new
word foe as antonym of friend.

1036
01:18:10,454 --> 01:18:13,122
Yes, how words develop
without anyone producing it.

1037
01:18:13,198 --> 01:18:16,363
-Award him with two!
-Two? Okay put!

1038
01:18:23,832 --> 01:18:24,408
Chinamaya,

1039
01:18:24,911 --> 01:18:29,680
teach them what you call Duryodhana,
Dushyasana, Karna and Shakuni together.

1040
01:18:30,075 --> 01:18:33,477
Well, Bad quartet! Repeat it!

1041
01:18:33,778 --> 01:18:35,077
Yes. Ba...

1042
01:18:37,820 --> 01:18:40,181
Come on, say it! Bad quartet!

1043
01:18:40,694 --> 01:18:42,087
Bada quarateet!

1044
01:18:43,250 --> 01:18:47,234
-Badaa quaraateete!
-Oh my God! Oh my God!

1045
01:18:47,470 --> 01:18:50,186
Oh my God! Oh my God!

1046
01:18:50,268 --> 01:18:51,226
-Shh!
-Shh!

1047
01:18:51,696 --> 01:18:54,324
-It's wrong to split a word.
-Why is it wrong?

1048
01:18:54,543 --> 01:18:58,576
We must split and kill those
quartet like they pronounce.

1049
01:18:59,934 --> 01:19:02,827
Oh my God! Oh my God!
[laughs]

1050
01:19:03,263 --> 01:19:07,474
My lord...
[groans]

1051
01:19:08,958 --> 01:19:12,435
Some human busted me.

1052
01:19:13,263 --> 01:19:14,985
He's young and tempered.

1053
01:19:16,019 --> 01:19:17,620
Human? A young man?

1054
01:19:18,361 --> 01:19:19,020
Strange! Strange!

1055
01:19:20,187 --> 01:19:21,302
-Hey Rambu
-Yes, my lord.

1056
01:19:21,559 --> 01:19:22,780
-Hey Jambu
-Yes, my lord.

1057
01:19:22,978 --> 01:19:26,095
I can't tolerate this any more.
Finish him with your magical powers.

1058
01:19:26,598 --> 01:19:28,254
-We'll knock him down and...
-And bring him to you.

1059
01:19:28,595 --> 01:19:30,018
-bring his dead body, my lord.
-Go now.

1060
01:19:31,094 --> 01:19:31,604
Wait!

1061
01:19:33,664 --> 01:19:37,063
I feel like seeing the young warrior.
Bring him alive.

1062
01:19:37,572 --> 01:19:38,115
What do you say, Chinamaya?

1063
01:19:39,506 --> 01:19:39,973
Go!

1064
01:19:43,622 --> 01:19:45,945
[demonic spell]

1065
01:20:06,918 --> 01:20:09,062
I'll spread from that side,
you spread from that side.

1066
01:20:10,356 --> 01:20:11,404
[demonic spell]

1067
01:20:22,616 --> 01:20:23,740
What's this danger, Dharuka?

1068
01:20:26,241 --> 01:20:28,114
Forest fire!
It's coming fast towards us!

1069
01:20:29,415 --> 01:20:35,362
Go back or seek refuge.

1070
01:20:39,159 --> 01:20:40,531
Looks like it's illusion!

1071
01:20:55,343 --> 01:20:58,459
-What do we do now?
-This is a wind missile!

1072
01:21:03,973 --> 01:21:08,677
[groaning]

1073
01:21:08,975 --> 01:21:14,945
[guffaws]

1074
01:21:21,227 --> 01:21:23,557
[guffaws]

1075
01:21:30,196 --> 01:21:32,361
Hail young hero! I appreciate you!

1076
01:21:32,885 --> 01:21:37,164
Your courage has moved me.
You are very enchanting.

1077
01:21:37,624 --> 01:21:40,991
Atlast you've gathered
courage and stood before me.

1078
01:21:41,523 --> 01:21:43,817
I'm also very happy. Come.

1079
01:21:44,197 --> 01:21:48,006
Hey boy! Your innocent face is
cooling my anger.

1080
01:21:48,312 --> 01:21:49,963
Your are a match to fight me.

1081
01:21:50,336 --> 01:21:52,947
Tell your name and seek refuge,
you'll become my associate.

1082
01:21:54,263 --> 01:21:56,662
Are you a warrior who
pleads on seeking refuge?

1083
01:21:57,257 --> 01:21:59,501
I'll make you seek refuge.
Watch out!

1084
01:22:01,833 --> 01:22:05,071
Aargh! You really hurt me!

1085
01:22:07,739 --> 01:22:11,126
But I don't feel like hitting back, boy!

1086
01:22:12,497 --> 01:22:15,081
Tell that you are incapable.

1087
01:22:15,796 --> 01:22:19,291
You can't just call me as a boy
and claim yourself to be an elder.

1088
01:22:19,580 --> 01:22:20,465
Show me your power.

1089
01:22:25,136 --> 01:22:29,897
I'm not getting enraged no matter how much
you provoke me. I feel pity about you boy.

1090
01:22:30,693 --> 01:22:35,376
O mother, ask your son to tell
his name and save his life.

1091
01:22:35,834 --> 01:22:39,446
-Son! Tell him your name.
-Impossible!

1092
01:22:39,857 --> 01:22:41,241
Scared of enemy and tell my name? No way!

1093
01:22:41,696 --> 01:22:42,512
Hey demon king!

1094
01:22:43,077 --> 01:22:45,462
Unable to win over me,
you've made this evil proposal.

1095
01:22:45,940 --> 01:22:47,808
You're cunning, coward,

1096
01:22:48,008 --> 01:22:50,118
-you don't have any pride.
-Hey! What's your arrogance?

1097
01:22:50,352 --> 01:22:53,829
You're going against me as if you're
here to test my power. Watch out!

1098
01:22:56,720 --> 01:22:58,133
[guffaws]

1099
01:22:59,636 --> 01:23:04,094
-Oh! He made our leader lose his mace.
-Oh! Suprising!

1100
01:23:06,297 --> 01:23:12,303
[guffaws]

1101
01:23:40,718 --> 01:23:41,156
[bangs]

1102
01:23:57,847 --> 01:23:58,348
[bangs]

1103
01:24:12,696 --> 01:24:14,234
[bangs]

1104
01:24:28,140 --> 01:24:28,827
[bangs]

1105
01:24:44,269 --> 01:24:44,929
[bangs]

1106
01:24:47,005 --> 01:24:47,491
Aargh!

1107
01:25:15,071 --> 01:25:15,832
[thud]

1108
01:25:16,366 --> 01:25:22,152
Abhimanyu... Abhimanyu!
My son.

1109
01:25:22,223 --> 01:25:23,285
He's just unconscious, madam.

1110
01:25:23,570 --> 01:25:26,193
Ensure the demon not attacks
again before he regains conscious.

1111
01:25:31,331 --> 01:25:37,332
"I'm Lord Krishna's sister
who rules over heaven and hell"

1112
01:25:41,081 --> 01:25:47,076
"I'm Arjuna's wife who is the
mightiest warrior with magical arrows"

1113
01:25:49,815 --> 01:25:53,055
"May this arrow kill the enemy"

1114
01:25:53,343 --> 01:25:57,812
and protect the heir of Pandavas

1115
01:25:59,779 --> 01:26:01,238
Forgive me mother, I seek your refuge.

1116
01:26:02,472 --> 01:26:03,771
It's an unwittingly committed mistake.

1117
01:26:04,397 --> 01:26:06,692
Please forgive me, mother.
It's an unwittingly committed mistake.

1118
01:26:07,033 --> 01:26:09,635
I'm Bhimasena's son, Ghatotkacha.

1119
01:26:09,956 --> 01:26:10,996
-Is it?
-Yes, mother.

1120
01:26:11,338 --> 01:26:13,577
It's an unwittingly committed mistake.
Please forgive me.

1121
01:26:16,321 --> 01:26:18,994
-Hey demon! Wherever you may be...
-Well...

1122
01:26:19,581 --> 01:26:21,037
Victory be yours brother!

1123
01:26:21,328 --> 01:26:23,097
I'm here under the
protection of mother.

1124
01:26:23,697 --> 01:26:26,449
Abhimanyu, he's your
elder brother Ghatotkacha.

1125
01:26:26,477 --> 01:26:27,422
-Huh?
-Yeah!

1126
01:26:27,799 --> 01:26:29,860
-Hi elder brother!
-Hi younger brother!

1127
01:26:33,357 --> 01:26:35,180
It is surprising!

1128
01:26:38,293 --> 01:26:40,150
I'm very elated, mother.
Extremely elated.

1129
01:26:40,245 --> 01:26:42,589
You've made a rare visit
to us. Got you at last.

1130
01:26:42,763 --> 01:26:43,796
I'll not leave you.

1131
01:26:44,600 --> 01:26:47,943
Son, I told you not to wage
any war. What's this commotion?

1132
01:26:48,521 --> 01:26:50,535
Who are these humans?
Why are you arresting them?

1133
01:26:51,093 --> 01:26:52,927
Not arresting but hosting, mother.

1134
01:26:53,715 --> 01:26:54,973
Do you know who she is?

1135
01:26:55,194 --> 01:26:59,613
She's queen of uncle Arjuna!
Subhadra Devi!

1136
01:26:59,935 --> 01:27:02,667
-Sister Hidambi.
-May God bless you, sister.

1137
01:27:02,868 --> 01:27:06,329
I'm seeing you for the
first time. Is he your son?

1138
01:27:06,645 --> 01:27:07,681
Yes, mother.

1139
01:27:08,383 --> 01:27:09,915
God bless you, son.

1140
01:27:09,947 --> 01:27:10,637
God bless you.

1141
01:27:11,285 --> 01:27:12,416
-Hey Rambu
-Yes, my lord.

1142
01:27:12,523 --> 01:27:13,668
-Hey Jambu
-Yes, my lord.

1143
01:27:14,115 --> 01:27:14,987
They are our friends!

1144
01:27:16,070 --> 01:27:17,431
frendz.

1145
01:27:18,094 --> 01:27:19,027
Bow to them!

1146
01:27:22,650 --> 01:27:23,443
Frendz.

1147
01:27:24,994 --> 01:27:28,498
-Madam Subhadra, I'll take leave now.
-See you.

1148
01:27:29,661 --> 01:27:30,637
-Hey Rambu
-Yes, my lord.

1149
01:27:30,729 --> 01:27:31,911
-Hey Jambu
-Yes, my lord.

1150
01:27:31,957 --> 01:27:33,404
Our friends must be
given a grand reception.

1151
01:27:34,146 --> 01:27:36,368
Arrange songs, dance and music!

1152
01:27:37,004 --> 01:27:37,763
Come... come.

1153
01:27:38,646 --> 01:27:39,116
Mother...

1154
01:27:41,354 --> 01:27:41,785
Brother...

1155
01:27:44,870 --> 01:27:46,242
Elders... Elders!

1156
01:27:46,483 --> 01:27:50,405
Why should we these
elders with us for the wedding?

1157
01:27:51,225 --> 01:27:54,295
Drona, Ashwathama and
Kripacharya are not even our relatives.

1158
01:27:54,637 --> 01:27:56,337
I struck off their names
at the begininng itself, brother.

1159
01:27:56,578 --> 01:27:59,940
Bheeshma and Vidhura are our grandfathers
amd we belong to their lineage.

1160
01:28:00,311 --> 01:28:02,704
Lord Krishna will definitely
ask why they haven't come.

1161
01:28:03,394 --> 01:28:05,169
What will be your reply, uncle?

1162
01:28:05,355 --> 01:28:08,768
What should we answer?
They are still on Pandavas side.

1163
01:28:08,872 --> 01:28:13,059
Hence, let's them that old men
are paralyzed or can't move.

1164
01:28:13,270 --> 01:28:15,664
Well said, Karna.
I struck off the oldies too.

1165
01:28:17,377 --> 01:28:21,436
By striking off all the names and if it is
just four of us who attends the wedding,

1166
01:28:21,693 --> 01:28:23,228
How could it be any glory?

1167
01:28:24,046 --> 01:28:28,814
Not just four of us, Duryodhana. All
your brothers would attend the marriage

1168
01:28:29,071 --> 01:28:32,269
All the hundred brothers are
enough, it will be very grand,

1169
01:28:32,519 --> 01:28:34,207
and we would can keep our word too.

1170
01:28:34,465 --> 01:28:36,855
Well said Uncle!
Then, what is our immediate duty?

1171
01:28:37,051 --> 01:28:38,011
Travel preparations.

1172
01:28:38,774 --> 01:28:40,500
Hail lord!

1173
01:28:40,930 --> 01:28:45,234
The grandfather must come
immediately to Lakshmana's room.

1174
01:28:45,474 --> 01:28:48,991
Uncle, go immediately.
He may've created a new problem.

1175
01:28:50,006 --> 01:28:53,031
No need, he himself is here.
Come son.

1176
01:28:57,690 --> 01:28:58,681
Character of youth!

1177
01:28:59,862 --> 01:29:03,530
You'll have a feeling of
socializing as your wedding is fixed.

1178
01:29:03,610 --> 01:29:05,788
Yes grandpa, I don't have any stage fear.

1179
01:29:06,025 --> 01:29:07,877
I'm came here because
I can speak in public.

1180
01:29:08,131 --> 01:29:09,236
I don't want to get married.

1181
01:29:09,437 --> 01:29:10,743
-What?
-Yes, father.

1182
01:29:11,073 --> 01:29:14,076
It's not bravery
without seeing the bride.

1183
01:29:15,304 --> 01:29:17,420
I was expecting this, Duryodhana.

1184
01:29:17,672 --> 01:29:21,196
Our boy forgot about this
respecting our decision.

1185
01:29:21,911 --> 01:29:22,852
Yes, now I remembered it.

1186
01:29:23,171 --> 01:29:27,754
Yes, grandson.
Princes like you must go and see any girl,

1187
01:29:27,895 --> 01:29:31,466
if you find them beautiful,
you should even fight Gods and win them.

1188
01:29:31,500 --> 01:29:31,982
Indeed.

1189
01:29:32,314 --> 01:29:35,102
Abhimanyu may hesitate but you wouldn't.

1190
01:29:35,453 --> 01:29:37,920
Let's go to Dwaraka immediately,

1191
01:29:38,021 --> 01:29:39,214
Upon reaching the bride's house,

1192
01:29:39,455 --> 01:29:41,643
I'll call the bride and you can meet her.

1193
01:29:42,753 --> 01:29:44,091
I'm sure you will like her.

1194
01:29:44,445 --> 01:29:47,057
Even if I don't like,
I must meet the bride before our wedding.

1195
01:29:47,223 --> 01:29:48,026
That's my vow!

1196
01:29:48,991 --> 01:29:52,680
-Alright, grandson. Get ready to travel.
-I'm always ready to travel.

1197
01:29:56,284 --> 01:29:59,956
[applaud]

1198
01:30:02,056 --> 01:30:02,809
-Son
-Mother

1199
01:30:03,166 --> 01:30:04,307
What's this senseless dancing?

1200
01:30:04,408 --> 01:30:06,471
Arrange a play that preaches moral.

1201
01:30:06,580 --> 01:30:07,356
I'll appreciate you.

1202
01:30:08,649 --> 01:30:10,811
You heard my mother's order,
right Chinamaya?

1203
01:30:11,339 --> 01:30:13,686
Yes. We have the story
of Mohini- Bhasmasura,

1204
01:30:13,911 --> 01:30:19,037
which preaches the moral about consquences
of granting boon to evil persons.

1205
01:30:20,650 --> 01:30:21,908
I'll arrange it. See and enjoy.

1206
01:30:22,521 --> 01:30:26,280
[casting a spell]

1207
01:30:33,141 --> 01:30:39,120
[music]

1208
01:35:26,216 --> 01:35:29,991
[applaud]

1209
01:35:42,812 --> 01:35:45,497
[knocks]
Sasi...

1210
01:35:45,952 --> 01:35:48,215
It's me! Open the door.

1211
01:35:49,532 --> 01:35:51,142
They came to get you dressed as a bride,

1212
01:35:51,561 --> 01:35:53,233
Why did you send them
out and closed the door?

1213
01:35:53,816 --> 01:35:54,524
Why don't you talk to me?

1214
01:35:55,513 --> 01:35:56,083
Open the door.

1215
01:35:56,951 --> 01:35:59,764
How many times do I've to tell you?
I don't like this marriage.

1216
01:36:03,013 --> 01:36:05,517
Sasi, there is nothing to do
with your consent or mine.

1217
01:36:05,844 --> 01:36:07,515
Don't think your protests
will cancel this marriage.

1218
01:36:07,888 --> 01:36:08,893
The groom's family is coming.

1219
01:36:09,387 --> 01:36:11,578
Your objections will not
be accepted. Be careful.

1220
01:36:12,023 --> 01:36:13,340
Get through it happily.

1221
01:36:14,622 --> 01:36:15,848
Happily?

1222
01:36:16,208 --> 01:36:19,341
You dashed my hopes, broke my heart,

1223
01:36:19,566 --> 01:36:23,067
and spoilt my mind.
Infact I don't want to live at all.

1224
01:36:23,167 --> 01:36:25,350
What are you saying, Sasi?

1225
01:36:25,964 --> 01:36:26,531
What happened, sister?

1226
01:36:26,692 --> 01:36:29,650
What could it be? Your ideas which you've
pitched into her mind since childhood,

1227
01:36:29,684 --> 01:36:30,694
are taking toll on me now.

1228
01:36:31,170 --> 01:36:33,276
Don't get angry, sister-in-law.
She is just a little girl.

1229
01:36:33,656 --> 01:36:37,176
Give her little time to calm down.

1230
01:36:37,508 --> 01:36:41,237
You will see her excited and
enthusiastic by tomorrow.

1231
01:36:41,246 --> 01:36:44,108
Whatever, Krishna. I'm always optimistic
because you solve all the things.

1232
01:36:44,858 --> 01:36:48,291
It's your responsibility to conduct
this marriage without any hitch.

1233
01:36:55,174 --> 01:36:57,881
What is this, Sasi?

1234
01:36:58,970 --> 01:37:00,519
[weeping]

1235
01:37:01,904 --> 01:37:04,226
Alright, you will know it tomorrow.

1236
01:37:12,989 --> 01:37:18,917
[music]

1237
01:37:32,649 --> 01:37:37,005
"I'm living just for you"

1238
01:37:37,610 --> 01:37:42,152
"In this sorrow of separation
and hopelessness"

1239
01:37:42,260 --> 01:37:46,297
"I'm living just for you"

1240
01:37:51,589 --> 01:37:55,957
"Even if moonlight turns dark"

1241
01:37:56,375 --> 01:38:01,165
"and if there is complete
darkness in my heart"

1242
01:38:01,366 --> 01:38:02,370
"I'm living just for you"

1243
01:38:05,702 --> 01:38:11,641
[music]

1244
01:38:20,205 --> 01:38:24,705
"Isn't separation of sorrow a solace?"

1245
01:38:24,931 --> 01:38:29,238
"Isn't thinking of love always sweet?

1246
01:38:29,633 --> 01:38:33,876
"Isn't separation of sorrow a solace?"

1247
01:38:34,246 --> 01:38:38,569
"Isn't thinking of love always sweet?

1248
01:38:38,937 --> 01:38:43,537
"In this time of separation,"

1249
01:38:43,746 --> 01:38:48,104
"Can't you see our love getting stronger?"

1250
01:38:48,574 --> 01:38:52,689
"I'm thinking about you"

1251
01:38:53,239 --> 01:38:57,625
"In my heart and mind"

1252
01:38:57,872 --> 01:39:02,229
"I'm thinking about you"

1253
01:39:02,668 --> 01:39:08,616
[music]

1254
01:39:14,771 --> 01:39:18,998
"Though my heart leaves with you"

1255
01:39:19,271 --> 01:39:24,089
"And my hopes vanish"

1256
01:39:26,299 --> 01:39:30,905
"I keep thinking about our love"

1257
01:39:31,079 --> 01:39:35,390
"and holding on to this life"

1258
01:39:35,892 --> 01:39:40,159
"I'm living just for you"

1259
01:39:40,464 --> 01:39:46,427
[music]

1260
01:39:52,776 --> 01:39:57,186
"In reality or in a dream,"

1261
01:39:57,507 --> 01:40:01,912
"I worship you as my lady love"

1262
01:40:04,613 --> 01:40:09,245
"Even if the entire
world turns against me"

1263
01:40:09,354 --> 01:40:13,953
"You're mine"

1264
01:40:14,211 --> 01:40:18,420
"I'm thinking about you"

1265
01:40:18,946 --> 01:40:23,752
"In this sorrow of separation
and hopelessness"

1266
01:40:23,828 --> 01:40:28,114
"I'm living just for you"

1267
01:40:33,718 --> 01:40:34,809
What?

1268
01:40:36,342 --> 01:40:38,018
He gave his word to get
Sasi married to Abhimanyu,

1269
01:40:38,291 --> 01:40:41,907
And he's he shamlessly breaking it to
get her married to Duryodhana's son?

1270
01:40:42,875 --> 01:40:45,204
How could Balarama being
your own brother insult you?

1271
01:40:45,696 --> 01:40:48,911
What can we do now, sister?
We lost all our wealth, right?

1272
01:40:49,480 --> 01:40:51,716
You just lost wealth not courage.
How can he even think like that?

1273
01:40:52,597 --> 01:40:55,355
How can the wealth worshippers
see courage, sister?

1274
01:40:56,070 --> 01:41:00,915
He even insulted by saying 'The Pandavas
are nothing compared to Kauravas'

1275
01:41:01,008 --> 01:41:02,310
Hey Rambu.
Hey Jambu.

1276
01:41:02,592 --> 01:41:03,615
Blow the war bugle!

1277
01:41:05,070 --> 01:41:06,436
Looks like son has heard us.

1278
01:41:07,123 --> 01:41:10,117
Son... Son.

1279
01:41:10,436 --> 01:41:14,337
My dear associates,
get ready with your armies and weapons.

1280
01:41:14,535 --> 01:41:15,884
We are going to war now.

1281
01:41:15,926 --> 01:41:20,258
Hail leader!

1282
01:41:20,851 --> 01:41:23,374
Whom are you waging a war against,
brother? I'll also join you.

1283
01:41:23,609 --> 01:41:26,103
Why do you toil when I'm there, brother?
My dear associates...

1284
01:41:26,303 --> 01:41:28,733
Son... Son!

1285
01:41:29,581 --> 01:41:33,088
I heard you, mother.
Not only did he break the promise,

1286
01:41:33,181 --> 01:41:38,313
but joined hands with those evil Kauravas
and belittled my world famous father.

1287
01:41:38,538 --> 01:41:41,978
These Yadavas are very proud and arrogant!

1288
01:41:42,179 --> 01:41:44,043
I'll avenge them by

1289
01:41:44,252 --> 01:41:48,688
wiping off both the Yadavas and
the Kauravas together in one go.

1290
01:41:49,035 --> 01:41:52,253
"They've grew contempt"

1291
01:41:52,461 --> 01:41:56,411
"and commited a terrible betrayal."

1292
01:41:56,568 --> 01:42:01,411
"Till I see their end"

1293
01:42:01,792 --> 01:42:05,809
"I, mighty Ghatothkach won't sleep"

1294
01:42:05,901 --> 01:42:11,324
"I pledge to wipe off
the entire Kuru clan"

1295
01:42:11,433 --> 01:42:15,568
-"and end their treachery"
-Hail leader!

1296
01:42:15,793 --> 01:42:19,345
Hail leader!

1297
01:42:19,696 --> 01:42:23,767
Son, it is the same if either of you
wages the war against my brother.

1298
01:42:23,853 --> 01:42:25,050
Won't it bring a bad name to me?

1299
01:42:25,744 --> 01:42:30,197
Then, I'll go to Hastinapuram
and finish at least Kauravas.

1300
01:42:30,278 --> 01:42:33,533
You can't kill them, son.
Your father has made vows.

1301
01:42:33,743 --> 01:42:35,617
The Kauravas must live to die
in the hands of the Pandavas.

1302
01:42:35,933 --> 01:42:37,604
Did you see, brother?

1303
01:42:37,798 --> 01:42:40,851
Our mothers' words have
made our strengths useless.

1304
01:42:42,059 --> 01:42:44,630
Follow my orders, son.
I'll appreciate you.

1305
01:42:45,268 --> 01:42:46,204
Go to Dwaraka,

1306
01:42:46,525 --> 01:42:48,619
use your magical powers
and bring Sasirekha here.

1307
01:42:48,913 --> 01:42:50,338
I'll get her married to him.

1308
01:42:50,852 --> 01:42:53,422
Good, your order will be
implemented, mother.

1309
01:42:53,466 --> 01:42:54,302
I'll go immediately.

1310
01:42:54,985 --> 01:42:57,958
-My dear associates!
-Hail leader!

1311
01:42:58,658 --> 01:42:59,878
-Son!
-Mother!

1312
01:43:00,221 --> 01:43:04,656
I'll let you go only if you promise,
not to hurt or harm anyone there.

1313
01:43:05,530 --> 01:43:07,788
-My brother, Sri Krishna...
-Is he a friend?

1314
01:43:07,819 --> 01:43:09,188
My respects to him.

1315
01:43:09,396 --> 01:43:14,312
-Upon reaching there, meet him...
-Not just meeting, worship him.

1316
01:43:14,453 --> 01:43:15,582
He'll be pleased.

1317
01:43:15,892 --> 01:43:19,042
-He will tell you the plan.
-So be it.

1318
01:43:19,258 --> 01:43:21,042
Hail mother!

1319
01:43:23,883 --> 01:43:27,420
Hey Brother! You shall protect
them till I come back return.

1320
01:43:27,916 --> 01:43:29,160
As you say, brother.

1321
01:43:31,382 --> 01:43:35,533
Hail leader!

1322
01:44:29,931 --> 01:44:35,941
[humming]

1323
01:44:40,474 --> 01:44:41,503
What's this?

1324
01:44:42,223 --> 01:44:45,083
Move I say. Move! Who are you?

1325
01:44:45,437 --> 01:44:51,381
[groaning]

1326
01:44:59,175 --> 01:45:03,874
[people laughing]

1327
01:45:31,549 --> 01:45:35,233
How am I to find Sasirekha among
them? How can I identify her?

1328
01:45:36,927 --> 01:45:38,277
I came without knowing any details.

1329
01:45:41,155 --> 01:45:44,594
I'm in the same dilemma my
uncle Hanuman had in Lanka.

1330
01:45:52,888 --> 01:45:57,454
"May you live forever and be happy"

1331
01:45:57,654 --> 01:46:02,120
"May you live forever and be happy"

1332
01:46:02,364 --> 01:46:04,608
"What's on the other side is not here"

1333
01:46:04,780 --> 01:46:06,922
"What's here is not
there on the other side"

1334
01:46:07,123 --> 01:46:09,362
"What's on the other side is not here"

1335
01:46:09,571 --> 01:46:11,644
"What's here is not
there on the other side"

1336
01:46:11,901 --> 01:46:14,204
"I'm there on the other side"

1337
01:46:14,212 --> 01:46:16,423
"It's me even in here"

1338
01:46:16,686 --> 01:46:18,732
"I'm there on the other side,
it's me even in here"

1339
01:46:18,772 --> 01:46:23,682
"May you live forever and be happy"

1340
01:46:24,201 --> 01:46:26,396
"Big fish will eat small fish"

1341
01:46:26,652 --> 01:46:28,662
"Big illusion will envelop smaller one"

1342
01:46:28,961 --> 01:46:31,147
"Big fish will eat small fish"

1343
01:46:31,224 --> 01:46:33,325
"Big illusion will envelop smaller one"

1344
01:46:33,449 --> 01:46:37,666
"That'll vanish.
This will vanish."

1345
01:46:38,052 --> 01:46:40,061
"That'll vanish.
This will vanish."

1346
01:46:40,362 --> 01:46:45,098
"May God bless you"

1347
01:46:46,007 --> 01:46:50,200
"You came without information
and you'll go unnoticed"

1348
01:46:50,309 --> 01:46:53,989
"You came without information
and you'll go unnoticed"

1349
01:46:54,337 --> 01:46:58,116
"This is enlightment"

1350
01:46:58,515 --> 01:47:02,289
-"This is enlightment..."
-Hey grandpa.

1351
01:47:03,108 --> 01:47:05,606
Your enlightment is good, but
tell me who you really are?

1352
01:47:06,675 --> 01:47:09,373
-Oh! Is it you?
-Yes.

1353
01:47:09,474 --> 01:47:11,179
Don't you know who I am?

1354
01:47:11,422 --> 01:47:12,446
That's why I'm asking, right?

1355
01:47:12,625 --> 01:47:14,823
An ignorant person will
not learn even if taught.

1356
01:47:14,900 --> 01:47:16,902
Hey grandpa! Stop your argument.

1357
01:47:17,124 --> 01:47:18,377
I don't care who you may be,

1358
01:47:19,598 --> 01:47:23,254
Just tell me,
where can I find Sasirekha?

1359
01:47:24,714 --> 01:47:26,807
What! Asking my help and shouting at me.

1360
01:47:27,137 --> 01:47:30,456
Tell me your name and seek
refuge humbly. I'll show you.

1361
01:47:30,557 --> 01:47:32,905
Hey grandpa! Who do you think I'm?
Be careful.

1362
01:47:33,457 --> 01:47:34,536
I can't hold my anger long,

1363
01:47:34,785 --> 01:47:36,558
I'll drown you and your
Dwaraka in the ocean.

1364
01:47:36,653 --> 01:47:39,345
Wow! Are you very powerful?

1365
01:47:39,685 --> 01:47:40,746
Why don't you tell me that?

1366
01:47:41,153 --> 01:47:44,127
You needn't do such great things,

1367
01:47:44,183 --> 01:47:49,801
I'm old and can't walk.
Carry me, I'll show you Sasirekha.

1368
01:47:49,936 --> 01:47:53,150
That's better. Get up!

1369
01:47:53,427 --> 01:47:58,139
"May God bless you!"

1370
01:47:58,881 --> 01:48:03,820
"May God bless you!"

1371
01:48:08,975 --> 01:48:09,746
You're so heavy!

1372
01:48:10,459 --> 01:48:13,674
You threatened to drown Dwaraka.
Can't you carry me?

1373
01:48:20,941 --> 01:48:23,416
[chuckles]

1374
01:48:23,751 --> 01:48:25,216
Carry me son... carry me.

1375
01:48:31,286 --> 01:48:34,346
Did you eat elephants for dinner?
What's the magic?

1376
01:48:34,447 --> 01:48:36,363
"Big illusion will envelop smaller one"

1377
01:48:36,604 --> 01:48:38,742
"That'll vanish.
This will vanish."

1378
01:48:39,151 --> 01:48:41,062
"I'm there on the other side.
It's me even in here"

1379
01:48:41,235 --> 01:48:42,917
"I'm everything"

1380
01:48:43,219 --> 01:48:48,023
Oh! I got it! I bow before you!

1381
01:48:51,552 --> 01:48:54,862
I bow before you, Lord Krishna!

1382
01:48:55,022 --> 01:48:58,622
Bless you!

1383
01:48:59,197 --> 01:49:01,611
I'm blessed, waiting for your order.

1384
01:49:03,983 --> 01:49:06,118
Your next duty is...

1385
01:49:07,265 --> 01:49:10,505
Tranfigure yourself as Sasirekha
and get married to Lakshmana Kumara.

1386
01:49:11,025 --> 01:49:12,537
Teach the Kauravas a lesson.

1387
01:49:14,086 --> 01:49:15,786
Divine instruction!

1388
01:49:16,136 --> 01:49:16,622
Myna,

1389
01:49:19,045 --> 01:49:21,527
From now, you're his favourite maid.

1390
01:49:22,483 --> 01:49:23,150
No problem.

1391
01:49:25,915 --> 01:49:27,947
-Can I take leave now?
-Be careful, nephew.

1392
01:49:29,344 --> 01:49:31,209
Myna, show me the way to my harem.

1393
01:50:05,699 --> 01:50:09,775
Madam Sairekha...
Madam Sasirekha...

1394
01:50:24,184 --> 01:50:29,783
Hail Lord Krishna!
Hail Lord Krishna!

1395
01:50:32,140 --> 01:50:34,222
Hail mother!

1396
01:50:34,303 --> 01:50:36,774
Wow! What a beauty!

1397
01:50:36,782 --> 01:50:38,056
Your daughter-in-law is very beautiful.

1398
01:50:39,131 --> 01:50:42,441
-You didn't make a mess there, right son?
-No mother... not at all.

1399
01:50:42,600 --> 01:50:44,323
Everything went off peacefully.

1400
01:50:45,792 --> 01:50:48,045
Lord Krishna's blessings, mother.

1401
01:50:48,861 --> 01:50:52,043
I've to go back,
host the Kauravas,

1402
01:50:52,068 --> 01:50:55,514
And marry Lakshmana Kumara.

1403
01:50:56,055 --> 01:50:57,486
-You?
-Yes mother, I have to.

1404
01:50:59,456 --> 01:51:01,987
Sister-in-law is waking up.
I'll take leave.

1405
01:51:06,403 --> 01:51:10,381
Dashed my hopes and spoilt my mind.

1406
01:51:12,092 --> 01:51:14,007
I don't want to live.

1407
01:51:14,515 --> 01:51:19,474
-Sasi... Sasi...
-Poor girl is still lamenting.

1408
01:51:19,815 --> 01:51:24,484
Sasi, look! It's me!

1409
01:51:25,926 --> 01:51:29,235
Aunt! How did you come here?

1410
01:51:29,679 --> 01:51:31,961
I didn't come.
It's who came to our place.

1411
01:51:32,735 --> 01:51:33,263
Me?

1412
01:51:37,403 --> 01:51:38,134
Where are we?

1413
01:51:38,824 --> 01:51:41,689
Don't get scared, I'll tell you.
Get up dear.

1414
01:51:44,788 --> 01:51:47,256
Did you hear me?
Ruin the wedding.

1415
01:51:48,102 --> 01:51:49,363
-Chinamaya
-My leader!

1416
01:51:49,587 --> 01:51:51,375
Use your magical powers and illusion

1417
01:51:51,689 --> 01:51:54,127
And build a guest city
for Kauravas in Dwaraka.

1418
01:51:54,227 --> 01:51:54,989
Yes

1419
01:51:55,231 --> 01:51:57,602
Spellbound them with your magic.

1420
01:51:57,707 --> 01:51:58,421
Hail leader!

1421
01:51:59,490 --> 01:52:00,575
-Hey Rambu
-My lord

1422
01:52:00,599 --> 01:52:01,536
-Hey Rambu
-My lord

1423
01:52:01,674 --> 01:52:04,415
Use your intelligence and
teach Kauravas a fitting lesson.

1424
01:52:05,433 --> 01:52:07,870
-Hosting a wedding is a tough task.
-But ruining it is a piece of cake.

1425
01:52:07,946 --> 01:52:13,787
[cheering]
Stop!

1426
01:52:14,782 --> 01:52:15,188
Get going!

1427
01:52:23,202 --> 01:52:24,126
Where's my brother?

1428
01:52:26,140 --> 01:52:26,562
Brother!

1429
01:52:53,155 --> 01:52:58,061
Beau got beaten up!

1430
01:52:58,262 --> 01:52:58,838
Who is it?

1431
01:53:00,409 --> 01:53:04,161
Sasi, how did you come here?
-Stay away.

1432
01:53:04,396 --> 01:53:06,859
Calling me now by leaving me in solitude.

1433
01:53:07,475 --> 01:53:08,578
-What is this, Sasi?
-Stay away.

1434
01:53:09,403 --> 01:53:10,142
Why are you so angry?

1435
01:53:10,758 --> 01:53:14,253
Don't you know I didn't take
chances respecting elders' words.

1436
01:53:14,472 --> 01:53:17,024
Fair enough! You must get a
good name for respecting elders,

1437
01:53:17,551 --> 01:53:19,497
and I must get bad name
for going against elders.

1438
01:53:19,706 --> 01:53:22,522
Enough, good bye to you and your love.

1439
01:53:22,672 --> 01:53:23,715
Now, it's brotherly love between us.

1440
01:53:23,988 --> 01:53:25,681
Sasi! What are you saying?

1441
01:53:25,996 --> 01:53:27,459
That's it.

1442
01:53:28,563 --> 01:53:30,628
I can't bear your sorrows or
pangs of separation any more.

1443
01:53:31,235 --> 01:53:33,983
I promised to marry Lakshmana
Kumara. And I'll stick to my word.

1444
01:53:35,044 --> 01:53:36,287
Is it my Sasi who is saying this?

1445
01:53:36,778 --> 01:53:40,095
No, I'm a brand new Sasi.
Totally changed.

1446
01:53:40,543 --> 01:53:43,183
I'll marry Lakshmana Kumara,
ride on elephant,

1447
01:53:43,261 --> 01:53:46,108
-and go to palace in a procession.
-Sasi, what's this nasty?

1448
01:53:46,414 --> 01:53:49,435
-Are you possessed by ghost?
-Not ghost but demon.

1449
01:53:50,036 --> 01:53:54,395
But now, it's brotherly love between us.
Come brother. Come.

1450
01:53:57,250 --> 01:53:58,845
I'm really very lucky, dear.

1451
01:53:58,944 --> 01:54:02,161
Krishna, Rukmini,
Balarama, Revathi,

1452
01:54:02,222 --> 01:54:03,196
everyone will come to my home for you.

1453
01:54:03,932 --> 01:54:06,399
Aunt... where is my brother-in-law?

1454
01:54:06,455 --> 01:54:09,277
I'm coming, sister-in-law.
Come, brother.

1455
01:54:14,876 --> 01:54:15,812
Did you see, brother?

1456
01:54:16,435 --> 01:54:18,308
Leave me to Lakshmana Kumara,

1457
01:54:18,501 --> 01:54:19,433
and you take your Sasi.

1458
01:54:20,237 --> 01:54:22,050
[chuckles]

1459
01:54:22,133 --> 01:54:24,612
Is this Lord Krishna's
instruction too, son?

1460
01:54:25,149 --> 01:54:26,145
Yes, mother.

1461
01:54:26,520 --> 01:54:31,415
Only God knows how that groom
is going to bear me as a bride.

1462
01:54:33,777 --> 01:54:35,912
How about brother-in-law's voice, aunt?

1463
01:54:37,495 --> 01:54:41,876
Don't worry about me, sister-in-law,
take good care of him.

1464
01:54:42,875 --> 01:54:46,222
Auspicious time is nearing,
I'm leaving now.

1465
01:54:46,788 --> 01:54:47,886
