It's awesome!

1955
02:31:55,423 --> 02:31:56,618
-Oh man!
-Aah!

1956
02:31:57,962 --> 02:32:03,976
-Ouch!
-Ouch!

1957
02:32:05,869 --> 02:32:06,740
[groans]

1958
02:32:07,571 --> 02:32:08,454
Oh no!

1959
02:32:15,354 --> 02:32:17,546
-Oh god!
-Aah!

1960
02:32:18,568 --> 02:32:23,789
[groans continue]

1961
02:32:27,024 --> 02:32:32,668
[music]

1962
02:32:37,228 --> 02:32:38,586
-Oh!
-Whoa!

1963
02:32:49,945 --> 02:32:52,882
[knocks]
Sarma! Sastry! The door.

1964
02:32:54,109 --> 02:32:56,242
Hey guys! Open the door.

1965
02:32:56,708 --> 02:32:57,776
[knocks]
Oh!

1966
02:32:59,735 --> 02:33:00,827
Open the door!

1967
02:33:01,459 --> 02:33:02,608
Open it... open it.

1968
02:33:04,361 --> 02:33:05,778
I know how to... wait!

1969
02:33:08,725 --> 02:33:12,739
-Oh Shiva!
-Oh Shiva!

1970
02:33:14,528 --> 02:33:17,436
Sarathy? Is it you who fell?

1971
02:33:18,021 --> 02:33:21,874
Fell? I was doing somersaults.
- Is it? Get up.

1972
02:33:22,019 --> 02:33:24,775
Why are you sitting in a corner
leaving the carpet and foam bed?

1973
02:33:25,069 --> 02:33:27,924
-Oh! That's for men like you.
-Please, go ahead.

1974
02:33:28,198 --> 02:33:29,479
Okay.

1975
02:33:31,097 --> 02:33:36,123
-Oh Shiva!
-Oh Shiva!

1976
02:33:39,684 --> 02:33:42,392
What's this?
Is it a place to keep your slippers?

1977
02:33:42,660 --> 02:33:45,328
-Do you've any sense?
-No, we didn't keep it there.

1978
02:33:45,610 --> 02:33:47,426
If not, did they come here on their own?

1979
02:33:49,746 --> 02:33:51,404
Maybe, we didn't see.

1980
02:33:58,075 --> 02:34:00,102
Wow! Foam bed!

1981
02:34:00,864 --> 02:34:03,656
What a luxury!

1982
02:34:05,585 --> 02:34:09,145
Amazing! Heavenly!

1983
02:34:09,318 --> 02:34:10,690
What a great comfort!

1984
02:34:11,778 --> 02:34:13,402
Did you see the foam bed?

1985
02:34:15,078 --> 02:34:16,436
Heaven... it's heaven.

1986
02:34:39,664 --> 02:34:40,951
Oh God!

1987
02:34:42,253 --> 02:34:43,623
Just a while ago,
you laughed loud at me.

1988
02:34:43,811 --> 02:34:46,014
Now, it's nothing. Very good.

1989
02:34:50,256 --> 02:34:56,192
Oh no! Ouch! Oh God!

1990
02:35:07,070 --> 02:35:08,412
Oh God!

1991
02:35:11,378 --> 02:35:15,777
-May you be blessed with peace!
-May you be blessed with peace!

1992
02:35:23,327 --> 02:35:24,741
What brings you at this hour?

1993
02:35:26,443 --> 02:35:31,396
After meeting the bride, I'm confused.

1994
02:35:32,460 --> 02:35:34,236
I feel like cancelling this marriage.

1995
02:35:34,533 --> 02:35:37,996
Did you see? That's Krishna's magic.

1996
02:35:38,361 --> 02:35:39,795
He made Sasi to act like this

1997
02:35:40,037 --> 02:35:45,052
so that we'll cancel
this wedding ourselves.

1998
02:35:45,958 --> 02:35:47,906
Can we fall into his trap?

1999
02:35:48,734 --> 02:35:52,435
Let the marriage be over,
everything would come in line.

2000
02:35:54,407 --> 02:35:55,262
Understood, mother?

2001
02:35:55,578 --> 02:35:57,844
At the same time when I
tie the knot over there,

2002
02:35:58,022 --> 02:36:00,849
Abhimanyu should do the same
here and it is Lord Krishna's order.

2003
02:36:01,335 --> 02:36:02,710
In my brother's absence?

2004
02:36:02,754 --> 02:36:06,322
No need to doubt it,
he'll be here as well as there.

2005
02:36:06,422 --> 02:36:07,266
Omnipresent.

2006
02:36:08,150 --> 02:36:10,862
I'll go now and ruin that wedding,

2007
02:36:11,055 --> 02:36:14,751
I'll be here with Balarama and others
in time to bless the new couple.

2008
02:36:14,826 --> 02:36:16,840
I'll purify our ashram, mother.

2009
02:36:16,871 --> 02:36:19,237
Do it son, I'll appreciate you.

2010
02:36:19,737 --> 02:36:21,521
Hail Lord Krishna!

2011
02:36:27,790 --> 02:36:33,609
[trumpets]

2012
02:36:34,092 --> 02:36:40,037
[wedding percussions]

2013
02:36:49,581 --> 02:36:52,486
"We are happy that"

2014
02:36:52,804 --> 02:36:56,306
"Sasirekha is the bride"

2015
